PN,31201
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782245910
OL,3,CUK to see more intense tropical-style
OL,4,Cthunderstorms later this week
OL,6,FIt was a noisy night for many of us,
OL,7,Fwith over 29,000 lightning strikes
OL,8,Frecorded by the Met Office in the last
OL,9,F24 hours.
OL,11,FAnd it looks like further severe
OL,12,Fthunderstorms are likely in the coming
OL,13,Fdays as warm, humid air continues to
OL,14,Ffeed volatile conditions across the UK.
OL,16,FThis means our weather conditions will
OL,17,Fbe similar to those in countries such
OL,18,Fas Singapore and Florida - places that
OL,19,Fare known for having prolonged and
OL,20,Fintense thunderstorms.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782245910
OL,3,CUK to see more intense tropical-style
OL,4,Cthunderstorms later this week
OL,6,FHere's why these storms are so severe
OL,7,Fand when exactly we can expect the
OL,8,Fnext downpours.
OL,10,FWhat caused the storms last night?
OL,12,FThe violent thunderstorms were caused
OL,13,Fby a surge of warm, moist, and
OL,14,Fincreasingly unstable air moving
OL,15,Facross the country.
OL,17,FWhen this type of air mass arrives, it
OL,18,Fcreates ideal conditions for them to
OL,19,Fdevelop. As the ground heats up during
OL,20,Fthe day, warm air rises rapidly
OL,21,Fthrough the atmosphere.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782245910
OL,3,CUK to see more intense tropical-style
OL,4,Cthunderstorms later this week
OL,6,FWhen this rising air is very humid, it
OL,7,Fbecomes buoyant and unstable, allowing
OL,8,Ftall cumulonimbus storm clouds to form.
OL,10,FInside these clouds, collisions
OL,11,Fbetween ice particles generate
OL,12,Felectrical charges, eventually
OL,13,Freleasing them as lightning.
OL,15,FIs this unusual for us?
OL,17,FWhile the UK regularly experiences
OL,18,Fsummer thunderstorms triggered by
OL,19,Fheatwaves and humid air, having nearly
OL,20,F30,000 lightning strikes in a single
OL,21,Foutbreak is pretty notable.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782245910
OL,3,CUK to see more intense tropical-style
OL,4,Cthunderstorms later this week
OL,6,FThe thunder will typically occur when
OL,7,Fwarm, humid air from the Continent
OL,8,Fmeets unstable atmospheric conditions
OL,9,Fover the UK.
OL,11,FThis was the scenario last night - and
OL,12,Fthe heatwave is barely underway.
OL,14,FThe high number of lightning strikes
OL,15,Fis a sign of the atmosphere becoming
OL,16,Fincreasingly unstable ahead of hotter
OL,17,Fand more humid air moving in.
OL,19,FWhere was hit the hardest?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782245910
OL,3,CUK to see more intense tropical-style
OL,4,Cthunderstorms later this week
OL,6,FThe West Country, most notably
OL,7,FSomerset, was by far the worst-
OL,8,Faffected area. There, they recorded
OL,9,Fapproximately 18,540 lightning
OL,10,Fstrikes, according to the Met Office.
OL,12,FDensely populated areas in the south-
OL,13,Feast also saw severe thunder and
OL,14,Flightning, including Kent with 1,729
OL,15,Fstrikes, and 1,558 in London.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
